elements.2211.03026_eee700e45431062d6b8a2e215698d: The robustness and accuracy of a vision system for motion estimation of a tumbling target satellite are enhanced by an adaptive Kalman filter
elements.2211.03026_48366f7900824d6332629fee0f618: This allows a vision-guided robot to complete the grasping of the target even if occlusion occurs during the operation
elements.2211.03026_914c1d0c0e6dd36bea7469193f185: A complete dynamics model, including aspects of orbital mechanics, is incorporated for accurate estimation
elements.2211.03026_2689961b7e01c3ee3fe627d8ae82a: Based on the model, an adaptive Kalman filter is developed that estimates not only the system states but also all the model parameters such as the inertia ratio, center-of-mass, and the rotation of the principal axes of the target satellite
elements.2211.03026_63db00e21294fe31de43a7ae75dc5: An experiment is conducted by using a robotic arm to move a satellite mockup according to orbital mechanics while the satellite pose is measured by a laser camera system
elements.2211.03026_46037ce41ab4e96089926434d0da7: The measurements are sent to the Kalman filter, which, in turn, drives another robotic arm to grasp the target
elements.2211.03026_59a4a96d43b38dbd495eba9d31008: The results demonstrate successful grasping even if the vision system is blocked for several seconds.
elements.2211.03026_da843d1ba4faa55d20620c419b56d: Internationally, there has been growing interest in using space robotic systems for the on-orbit servicing of spacecraft
elements.2211.03026_9da7b866d28339eeae4549e33a340: In such missions, the accurate motion estimation of a free-falling target spacecraft is essential for guiding a robotic arm so as to capture the target
elements.2211.03026_b585ad8df748dec68d930bcd489ba: Different vision systems are available for the estimation of the pose (position and orientation) of moving objects
elements.2211.03026_84b99805e5e2920fe3151ef77bd8a: Among them, an active vision system such as the Neptec Laser Camera system (LCS) is preferable for its robustness in face of the harsh lighting conditions of space
elements.2211.03026_746c96c1a2994fe43b6dbd9458d36: As successfully verified during the STS-105 space mission, the 3D imaging technology used in LCS can indeed operate in space environment
elements.2211.03026_2fd874b14a1e186dcb9c3bf8935c8: The use of laser range data has also been proposed for the motion estimation of free-floating space objects
elements.2211.03026_aa6c6b223a99bfdeeddf5090cc171: All vision systems, however, provide discrete and noisy pose data at relatively low rate, typically 1
elements.2211.03026_8d3063408d57c5159bd0e0f61fa93: Hz, while the capture of a free-falling object is a difficult robotic task which requires real-time and accurate pose estimation
elements.2211.03026_012c73aa266ac6f443787eff4ebeb: Taking advantage of the simple dynamics of a free-floating object, researchers have employed different observers to track and predict the motion of a target satellite
elements.2211.03026_3b54e5403e2ab9153b88b23311499: In some circumstances, e.g., when there are occlusions, no observation data is available
elements.2211.03026_73e0c846baf129fde2a50e84cdc12: Therefore, long-term prediction of the motion of the object is needed for planning operations such as autonomous grasping of targets
elements.2211.03026_7a3309f4512ae022349568e30ddb2: The Kalman filter uses a dynamics model to compute a rough estimate of the system states, which is then corrected using a model of the sensor measurements to obtain the best estimate possible of the system states based on the present and past measurements
elements.2211.03026_92d5dfe70161cbfc7e350fa5d9c05: However, the applicability of the Kalman filtering technique rests on the accuracy of the dynamics and the measurement-noise models
elements.2211.03026_16fcddb87f6d556f725205a675d9b: In this work, we use the Euler-Hill equations to derive a discrete-time model that captures the evolution of the relative translational motions of a tumbling target satellite with respect to a chaser satellite which is free-falling in a nearby orbit
elements.2211.03026_29b74ddf4672d4aad5aa97a9aa6d1: Taking advantage of the structure of the model, we derive numerically efficient expressions for the state transition matrix and the covariance of the process noise, both of which are necessary for the Kalman filter
elements.2211.03026_283e409544102d8d41210597dd453: We also derive the sensitivity matrix of the observation and show that the observations of the translational and rotational displacements are coupled
elements.2211.03026_d5cf1725cc93333c35fabd4205451: Moreover, the kinematic properties of the unit-norm quaternions used to represent the relative orientation of the target satellite, is employed to derive the associated measurement-noise covariance
elements.2211.03026_28610fff72b52f3a079d9e044a3c5: quaternion noise while preserving the unit-norm property of the quaternion
elements.2211.03026_236a4ad0a263e27f1599d4c0cbdaa: This Kalman filter has been implemented in Matlab/Simulink and used in real-time to permit the autonomous capture of a tumbling satellite using a chaser arm
elements.2211.03026_074188859d670ae3e5921b5fc301b: The performance of the Kalman filter is such that it is possible to fully occlude the vision system and perform the capture of the satellite more than 20 seconds after the occlusion using only the output of the EKF to provide a prediction of the pose of the satellite.

elements.2211.03026_0803fbe32fba7886c18f87abe0dcf: A discrete-time adaptive estimator was developed for estimating the relative pose of two free-falling satellites that move in close orbits near each other using position and orientation data provided by a laser vision system
elements.2211.03026_23cc8007e7a888cc6ade51f45f07c: The covariance matrix of the measurement noise was modelled in a state-dependant form
elements.2211.03026_a8bc2be321c61cfa281deb7d70983: This model allows additive quaternion noise, while preserving the unit-norm property of the quaternion
elements.2211.03026_d23960d7cda584bc03bfd97c7faba: The effects of orbital mechanics was incorporated in the model-based estimator for both the accurate estimation and the prediction of the relative motion
elements.2211.03026_0c768c0123337619c39c5da81275c: The discrete-time model, including the state-transition matrix and the covariance of the process noise were derived in closed form suitable for implementing the extended Kalman filter in real time
elements.2211.03026_aef030938a44a712f65ba1fbf3a6f: Experimental results illustrating the autonomous capture of a tumbling satellite with an occluded vision system were reported
elements.2211.03026_d69462c8fafd94c32b5502df4d41d: The results demonstrated that the filter could accurately estimate and predict the states of the system for more than 20 seconds after the occlusion, thus permitting the successful capture of a tumbling satellite.
